<HEADLINE> UK Approves Ottawa Convention on Banning Landmines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The House of Commons in Britain
Friday approved a draft legislation, bringing the Ottawa
Convention on banning landmines into British law.
</P>
<P>
Under the new legislation, the British government will impose a
prison sentence of up to 14 years for anyone who uses, develops,
produces, buys, owns or transfers a landmine, or even assists,
encourages or induces any one else to do so.
</P>
<P>
However, one of its important clauses is to offer immunity for
British soldiers who might be involved in future joint overseas
military operations with allied forces that use landmines.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Labor government reportedly said earlier that it had
destroyed about half of its 1 million landmines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
