<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce Trent 700 Wins New Orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Airtours confirmed they will be
taking two further Trent 700 powered A330-200 aircraft in addition
to two A330-200s ordered last year, Rolls-Royce plc announced here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The latest aircraft will be delivered in the fourth quarter of
1999 and will be operated by its Scandinavian airline Premiair on
long haul routes, the company said.
</P>
<P>
The deal is worth approximately 50 million U.S. dollars to
Rolls-Royce. Airtours also has options on four A330-200 aircraft
which brings the market share for the engine on the A330 to 43
percent.
</P>
<P>
Premiair is the third new customer to select Rolls-Royce Trent
700 powered A330-200 aircraft in 1998, bringing the total number of
Trent 700 customers to 14.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce plc said that the Trent 700 has now flown over
250,000 hours in service, at a rate of up to 250 hours per
aircraft per month.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the engine will reach the half million
mark (500,000 hours) by the fourth quarter of 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
