<HEADLINE> Rolls-Royce Shares in Qatar V2500 Engine Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- International Aero Engines (IAE),
in which Rolls-Royce plc is a major shareholder, is to supply
Qatar Airways with V2500 engines for its new fleet of Airbus
Industrie A320 aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The order consists of six firm aircraft with options on an
additional five. The total value for the deal to Rolls-Royce is 55
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The purchased aircraft will be delivered from 2001 to 2005,
assuming all the options are converted, according to an
announcement Friday by Rolls-Royce plc.
</P>
<P>
The V2500 powered A320s will be used on Qatar's extensive
regional route network covering Middle East, Indian subcontinent
and Gulf area destinations, the company said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Rolls-Royce, IAE's partners include Pratt &AMP; Whitney,
the Japanese Aero Engines Corporation and MTU Daimler Benz.
</P>
