<HEADLINE> Blair Voices Support for Russia' Economic Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
Friday expressed strong support for Russia's economic reforms and
its efforts to avoid devaluation of the Russian currency rouble.
</P>
<P>
A Downing Street spokesman told reporters Friday that Russian
President Boris Yeltsin called Blair early Friday and "briefed the
prime minister on his discussions with the IMF (International
Monetary Fund)."
</P>
<P>
"The prime minister (Blair) expressed his strong support for
Yeltsin's efforts to continue economic reform and avoid
devaluation (of the Russian currency)," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Blair, Yeltsin reportedly had a series of telephone
conversations with other European leaders including German
Chancellor Helmut Kohl and French President Jacques Chirac to seek
support for fresh IMF loans to help Russia out of its financial
crisis. 
</P>
