the respect for the democratically-elected authority in the
country, the OAU chief stressed.
</P>
<P>
He noted that he changed views with President Chissano on
conflicts in Africa, especially the conflict in Angola, that
between Ethiopia and Eritrea and in the Comoros.
</P>
<P>
Ahead of his meeting with Chissano, Salim delivered a speech
in the Medical Institute of the University of Eduardo Mondlane,
emphasizing the importance of cultivating the culture promoting
peace.
</P>
<P>
On OAU's efforts in pursuing peace, stability and security in
the continent, he said that lasting peace could be maintained
only with popular participation. Salim will end his visit to
Mozambique on Saturday.  
