<HEADLINE> IPE Open Interest Tops Half Million for First Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Total open interest for all the
International Petroleum Exchange's (IPE) futures and options
contracts reached its highest level ever recorded Friday.
</P>
<P>
The IPE announced that the number of open positions reached
502,645 lots, topping the half million mark.
</P>
<P>
This is equivalent to 432 million barrels of oil (six times
more than daily world oil consumption) and 728 million therms of
natural gas (or 10 times daily UK gas consumption).
</P>
<P>
Open interest represents the number of positions outstanding,
that is, those that have not been canceled out by an equal and
opposite transaction.
</P>
<P>
The increase in open interest follows an exceptionally busy
first half of the year for the IPE. Overall traded volumes are up
about a third on the same period for last year.
</P>
<P>
Last month was the second busiest month ever in the exchange's
17-year history, with volumes averaging 81,025 lots a day.
</P>
<P>
The most active month ever recorded was also this year, when an
average of 83,255 lots a day were traded in March.
</P>
<P>
Richard Ward, executive vice president of the IPE, said, "Our
contracts have enjoyed a tremendous year to date, and we look
forward to achieving even more in the second half." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
