<HEADLINE> British Police Foil Bomb Attempt in Central London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- British police Friday successfully
foiled a bombing attempt by Irish dissident criminals in central
London only by minutes, according to BBC television reports.
</P>
<P>
John Grieve, chief of the Scotland Yard anti-terrorist branch,
said that four men were arrested in possession of explosives
intended to be used "within minutes."
</P>
<P>
British police acted on information from police in the Irish
Republic who are engaged in a joint operation against "dissident
republican groups."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Irish police arrested three suspects in the Irish
Republic and discovered shotguns and bomb parts in the operation.
</P>
</TEXT>
