<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Announces to Evict EPLF Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian government
announced Friday that it "has decided to evict members of the
Eritrean People's Liberation Front (EPLF) believed to pose
threats to national security."
</P>
<P>
The office of the Ethiopian government spokesperson is quoted
by the Ethiopian News Agency as saying that "the Ethiopian
government has gathered that EPLF has begun functioning through
its ordinary members reorganizing anew its structure in an
attempt threatening national security."
</P>
<P>
"EPLF has organized its members to raise funds, provide
intelligence services, involve in espionage and spread propaganda
to foster its war efforts," office said.
</P>
<P>
"Thus, members of the EPLF who have been rounded up today will
be sent to their country," the office said, adding that "the
measure does not apply to law abiding Eritreans who could lead
their life peacefully as usual."
</P>
<P>
Officials of the EPLF were deported on June 13, according to
the office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
