<HEADLINE> New Shipping Line Between Mainland And Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The first freight line between the
port city of Xiamen in east China's Fujian Province and the port
city of Kaohsiung in Taiwan opened today.
</P>
<P>
It will provide regular freighter service from Xiamen's Haicang
Port every Saturday.
</P>
<P>
An international freight company in Xiamen that was founded in
1997 will be in charge of the route. It already has freight
service to Japan, the Republic of Korea, and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Haicang, which is 163 nautical miles from Kaohsiung, is ideal
for direct shipping across the Taiwan Straits, says Lin Wenqing,
the company's general-manager.
</P>
<P>
He predicts that the company will have a big share in the
direct trade across the Straits in future. 
</P>
