<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index Hits New Low This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Stock Exchange (KSE)
Saturday hit a new low for the year, with the index shedding 31.4
points compared with Wednesday to close at 1,996.8 points, the
first time dropping below the 2,000-point level.
</P>
<P>
The volume, transactions and value all slipped with a total of
21.60 million shares over 715 deals against 29.52 million shares
over 1,016 deals Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The value of shares changed hands also fell to 5.54 million
Kuwaiti dinars (18.28 million U.S. dollars) from Wednesday's 7.66
million dinars (25.27 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Most analysts believe that a "wait and see" attitude adopted by
major dealers and the drop in oil prices are the main reasons for
the slump.
</P>
<P>
Some economists, however, insist that the Kuwaiti government
shoulder some blame for the slide in the stock market. The
government does not have a precise financial policy, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
