<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second Flood Peak on Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Yangtze River's second flood
peak passed through China's Jiangsu Province this morning as dykes
withstood another onslaught.
</P>
<P>
Water flow reached 53,500 cubic meters per second in Hubei
Province on July 3, then water levels went above the danger line.
</P>
<P>
The situation got worse in Jiangsu Province on July 9. On July
10, the water level at Nanjing reached 9.85 meters, 1.35 meters
above the danger line.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that dykes built in the past few years kept the
flood from doing any greater damage to the province. It has 520 km
of dykes that can handle the types of floods that occur every 50
years and another 235 km of dykes with concrete slopes.
</P>
<P>
The province plans to spend 2.35 billion yuan on dyke repairs
over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
During this flood season, the province also mobilized a million
people for the flood-control work, which also helped protect the
dykes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
