<HEADLINE> FIFA to Hire Specialists for 2002 Ticketing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- FIFA will hire specialists to draw up
better ticketing plans for the 2002 World Cup finals after receiving
criticism for their policy at this finals in France here, President
Sepp Blatter said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"In 2002, we will have specialists in ticketing to avoid the
situation we had here in France '98," Blatter told a news conference
here.
</P>
<P>
The French World Cup Organizing Committee (CFO) was blasted by the
European Union before the kick-off of the competition for allocating
too few tickets for other countries.
</P>
<P>
The CFO gave in to set up special hotlines for fans outside France
to book tickets.
</P>
<P>
But Blatter also slammed the national federations who failed to
return the unsold tickets to the French organizing committee as
indicated by the agreements.
</P>
<P>
The next World Cup finals will be co-hosted by Japan and South
Korea. 
</P>
