<HEADLINE> EU Lifts Ban on Imports of Bangladeshi Frozen Fish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has decided
to withdraw a ban on imports from 11 more Bangladeshi frozen-fish
exporting factories, a report reaching here Saturday said.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken at a meeting of the European Commission,
the executive body of the EU, in Belgium on July 7.
</P>
<P>
Early this year, the EU ended a ban on seven frozen-fish
processing factories in Bangladesh, nearly half a year after it
was imposed on importing frozen fish from Bangladesh in August
last year for "low quality," the report said.
</P>
<P>
Frozen seafood export, which earned the country 321 million
U.S. dollars in the 1996-97 fiscal year ending June 30, 1997, is
the third major foreign exchange earner of Bangladesh, following
the garments and the knitwear industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
