<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BIS Opens First Overseas Office in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Bank for International
Settlement (BIS) Saturday opened its representative office for
Asia and the Pacific in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
This is the first overseas office for the international
financial organization, which, founded in 1930, has previously
operated only from its headquarters in Basle, Switzerland, to
enhance international monetary and financial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
With the establishment of the regional office, the BIS aims to
strengthen its relations with central banks and monetary
authorities in the Asia-Pacific region and to improve the exchange
of information and data.
</P>
<P>
Central bank governors of major industrial countries and other
regional economies attended the opening ceremony here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, said in a following reception, "I believe
that the BIS, with its expertise and physical presence in this
geographic hub of Asia, should play an important role in
strengthening the financial systems in Asia during the recovery
period."
</P>
<P>
Headed by George Pickering, the BIS representative office was
opened here with six staff members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
