<HEADLINE> Gold Price in Hong Kong Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The gold price in Hong Kong fell
seven HK dollars to close at 2,674 HK dollars a tael Saturday,
according to Po Sang Bank, one of the major gold dealers in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
The gold price is equivalent to 289.70 U.S. dollars a troy
ounce, 0.74 U.S. dollars down from the previous close at
Saturday's exchange rate of one U.S. dollar to 7.7480 HK dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
