<HEADLINE> Zagallo Says The Brazilian Team Belongs to Him </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian team manager Mario Zagallo
said the Brazilian team belonged to him, not to anybody else.
</P>
<P>
"This team doesn't belong to the Brazilian Football Confederation
or to the technical staff. It belongs to me," said Zagallo.
</P>
<P>
"What we have accomplished in this World Cup gives me confidence
for the final against France. The success or failure of the
Brazilian team rests squarely on my shoulders. I will assume the
full consequence for my actions." said Zagallo.
</P>
<P>
"The final match will be decided during the 90 minutes of play
on Sunday. We cannot go back to Brazil without this World Cup,"
said Zagallo, "I hope that Sunday we will claim this trophy once
again, no one will prevent us from winning this fifth title. I
firmly believe we will succeed." 
</P>
</TEXT>
