<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia to Reduce Foreign Trade Deficit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslavian government
Friday decided to take measures to reduce the country's trade
deficit and to increase its foreign exchange reserves.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia will limit importation of daily consumer goods, and
control imports of cigarettes, coffee and alcohol so as to reduce
the outflow of foreign exchange, the local press reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The government will also introduce seasonal tariff rates on
agricultural imports to protect the country's own agricultural
production.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia's foreign trade deficit stood at 1.2 billion U.S.
dollars in the first half of this year, as compared to 2.43
billion dollars in the whole of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
