<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Launches Compulsory Education Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The State Compulsory Education
Project for Poverty-Stricken Regions was recently launched in
north china's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, according to the
local government.
</P>
<P>
The central and local governments will allocate special funds
totalling 670 million yuan over the next three years to carry out
the project, the major "aid the poor" education program in the
autonomous region's 51 Leagues or counties.
</P>
<P>
The funds will mainly be used to build 3,164 primary and middle
schools, improve the management levels in local schools, and
supplement teaching materials, desks, chairs and library books.
</P>
<P>
In addition, local education departments will sponsor a series
of training programs for primary school teachers.
</P>
<P>
The compulsory education program will be introduced to 70
percent the region's counties or leagues by the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
