<HEADLINE> India to Import LNG, Crude Oil From Qatar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 11 (Xinhua) -- India intended to buy liquid
natural gas (LNG) and crude oil from Qatar, according to a joint
statement signed here Friday by Indian Petroleum Minister V.
Ramamurithy and Qatari Energy and Industry Minister Abdula Bin
Hammed Al-Attiyah.
</P>
<P>
Al-Attiyah, who arrived here Wednesday, held discussions with
senior officials of the Indian Petroleum Ministry and chief
executives of Indian gas and petroleum corporations in the last
three days, the Hindu daily reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It was agreed that Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) would begin
negotiations with Qatar General Petroleum Corporation (QGPC), of
which Al-Attiyah is the chairman, for imports of up to 150,000
tons of liquefied petroleum gas.
</P>
<P>
IOC will also buy one trial cargo each of Qatar land crude and
Al Shaheen crude from QGPC and import crude oil based on the
results of the trial processing of these crudes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
