<HEADLINE> Guizhou Province Uses World Bank Loan for Poverty Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guizhou Province
used 336 million yuan of World Bank loan funds for poverty relief
over the years till the end of 1997, accounting for 40.52 percent
of the total World Bank loans to the province.
</P>
<P>
During the 1995-1999 period, the World Bank will have provided
539 million yuan for Guizhou, which is an important target of
World Bank poverty relief loans in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, the World Bank loans have been used in
various projects to improve low-yield fields (3446 ha.), to grow
economic crops (4524 ha.), to build highways (277 km.) and electric
transmission lines (271 km.), village primary schools (89900
sq.m.) and to provide drinking-water to 141,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The relief projects have covered 826 poverty-stricken villages
in 13 counties. About 95 percent of school-age children in these
areas are in classes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
