<HEADLINE> Western Opinion on Myanmar Criticized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar government strongly
criticized western opinion on Myanmar, according to an official
Information Sheet issued here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Information Sheet quoted a news release from the Myanmar
Embassy in Ottawa, Canada, as saying there have been some media
reports of impending political unrest in Myanmar in connection
with the re-opening of all schools and universities in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The news release said the reports are entirely without basis
and may even be called fictitious.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar government has always had deep concern for the
personal security of all politicians including Aung San Suu Kyi,
general secretary of National League for Democracy (NLD), as there
are known elements who are trying to create political unrest by
putting her to some form of bodily harm, the news release said.
</P>
<P>
It pointed out, "Any suggestion to the contrary must be
considered presumptuous and unnecessary, since 16 out of 17 armed
insurgent groups have returned to the legal fold in recent years
lowering all forms of tensions to unprecedented levels."
</P>
<P>
"Attempts to artificially create unrest and instability by
local politicians to suit their own ends are not likely to have
any popular support within the country," it declared. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
