<HEADLINE> Outbreak of Diseases Claim Another 92 in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of gastroenteritis,
diarrhea and dysentery has claimed another 92 lives in Bajura and
Humla districts of Nepal, press reports here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 77 people have died of gastroenteritis in the past
three weeks in four villages of Bajura district, western Nepal,
the Kantipur daily said.
</P>
<P>
A large number of people there were also affected by the
disease, it said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 15 died recently of diarrhea and dysentery in
various parts of Humla district in mid-western Nepal, The
Kathmandu Post said.
</P>
<P>
It said that in recent months, about 350 people have died of
hunger and respiratory diseases there.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that more than 500 people have died of
gastroenteritis, typhoid, fever and other diseases across the
country in the summer season.
</P>
<P>
Unhygienic conditions including unsafe drinking water are
blamed for the outbreak of various diseases.
</P>
<P>
Inadequate health facilities, in particular lack of medicine
and doctors in the remote and hilly areas, contribute to the death
toll. 
</P>
