<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nokia Increases Exposure in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Finnish-based mobile
communications giant Nokia has increased its exposure in both
north and south China by securing new contracts and expanding a
Guangdong joint venture.
</P>
<P>
Nokia consummated a landmark contract earlier this week with
the mobile communications arm of Tianjin Telecom in Tianjin, a
port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
The contract calls for Nokia to supply fiber optical
transmission equipment for the city's global mobile telephone
network.
</P>
<P>
The agreement marked Nokia's first order for related equipment
from China's telecommunications sector, and marked the company's
entry into new business areas in China.
</P>
<P>
Experts point out that Nokia provided technology will
effectively reduce the city's initial investment required to
install a mobile communications network.
</P>
<P>
The technology -- synchronous digital hierarchy (SDH) -- offers
high flexibility enabling mobile communications centers to operate
during the installation stage.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Nokia expanded the production capacity
of its joint venture in Dongguan, south China's Guangdong
Province, in late June this year. The project enabled the Dongguan
Nokia Mobile Telephone Co. Ltd. to expand its production of
peripherals to include mobile telephone sets. The joint venture is
currently producing Nokia's most recent mobile telephone sets.
</P>
<P>
A senior Nokia official said the latest developments
demonstrates the company's commitment to increasing investments
and expanding technological cooperation in China.
</P>
<P>
Nokia claimed that it sold 21.3 million mobile telephone sets
around the world in 1997, which accounted for 21 percent of the
global market for related items. The company has also captured a
similar share of the China market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China had over 16 million mobile telephone
users by the end of April.
</P>
<P>
Nokia has established six joint ventures and one solely-owned
production base in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
