<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Police Seize Suspected LTTE Lorry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Police in the capital city of
Colombo have seized a lorry suspected to belong to the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), police said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Police had received information that the LTTE was planning to
carry a powerful bomb to Colombo in a lorry loaded with rice. The
lorry came from the north of the island country and was detained
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the driver and the cleaner of the lorry were being
intensively grilled by police investigators.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Colombo police have rounded up about 20 Tamils
in a search operation in the city.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war against the government for a
separate state in the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
