<HEADLINE> Thailand to Send Observers to Cambodian election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Nine Thai observers to Cambodia's
election will be deployed to six Cambodian provinces in
cooperation with the United Nations Electoral Assistance
Secretariat (EAS), according to the Thai Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The mission, already approved by the Thai Cabinet, was in
accordance with a Cambodian government request for the
international community to send observers to the national poll on
July 26 to ensure it is free and fair.
</P>
<P>
They will be deployed in Bangteay Meanchhay, Kampong Chhnang,
kampong Speu, Kampot, Kandal and Phnom Penh which are represented
by a large number of members of Parliament, the Nation newspaper
reported.
</P>
<P>
The team, to be led by Nuttavudh Poetisaro, a Thai Foreign
Ministry official, will work in cooperation with the EAS and
observers from other countries.
</P>
<P>
The international observers are expected to cover about 1,500
of 11,000 polling stations throughout the country. 
</P>
