<HEADLINE> 28th World Diamond Congress to be Held in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The 28th World Diamond Congress
will be held from July 27-29 in Bangkok, the Bangkok Post reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time that the congress, organized every
two years by the World Federation of Diamond Bourses and the
International Diamond Manufacturers' Association, is to be held in
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 international diamond dealers' representatives will
attend the congress.
</P>
<P>
The gems and jewelry industry is Thailand's ninth-largest
export earner. Its top 10 overseas markets are the United States,
Belgium, Israel, Germany, Switzerland, France, Britain, Hong Kong,
Japan and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The industry employs more than 600,000 staff in Thailand,
including gem cutters and goldsmiths, and 7,000 diamond cutters.
</P>
