<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SDB Offers Loans to Aid Power Grids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank of
China (SDB) will offer loans worth seven billion yuan to Anhui
Power Corp within the next three to five years to bolster
construction of electricity power grids in this east China
province, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The loans will facilitate the building of the province's
central, urban and rural electrical power grids, according to an
agreement signed Friday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The bank, a policy bank established in 1994, is designed to
carry out the State's industrial policies and facilitate
infrastructure projects and basic industrial development.
</P>
<P>
Between 1994 and 1997, the bank injected an accumulated 26
billion yuan into electricity transformer and transmission
projects at annual average growth of 34.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
This year, SDB's loans to the electricity sector is expected to
reach 20 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
It also plans to loan 50 billion yuan to the construction of
rural power grids within three years, which is estimated to
account for 44.6 percent of the gross amount of fund needed for
the nationwide building of electricity projects in the
countryside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
