<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Female School Drop-outs Return to Classrooms in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 11 (Xinhua) -- More than 30,000 female school
drop-outs in Gansu Province have gone back to classrooms in
primary schools over the past six years.
</P>
<P>
The students have been helped by the "Spring Bud" Project
sponsored by the women's federations at various levels in the
province.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, nearly 97 percent of the school-aged girls in the
province are in school thanks to the project.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has set up six schools and 92 classes
for girls with funds raised for the "Spring Bud" project.
</P>
<P>
To promote the understanding of compulsory primary education,
local authorities have hosted nearly 5,000 training programs for
560,000 parents, governmental officials and educators.  
</P>
</TEXT>
