<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chilean Copper Exports To Asia Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Chilean copper exports to Asia
between January and April this year amounted to 688.5 million
U.S. dollars, down 40 percent compared with the same period of
last year, official figures showed Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the first four months of 1997, Chilean copper exports to
Asia accounted for 50.2 percent of its total copper export, but
the percentage dropped to 38.6 percent in the same period this
year.
</P>
<P>
Now, Asia dropped to the second place as a market for the
Chilean copper, giving up the first place to Europe, which
imported 719.6 million dollars worth of copper from Chile in the
first four months this year, marking a 2.2 percent increase from
last year.
</P>
<P>
The drop was attributed to a shrinking demand caused by the
Asian financial crisis. The statistics showed that Chilean copper
exports to Japan totaled 263.1 million dollars in the first four
months of the year, representing a 53.1 percent drop from the same
period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Sales to South Korea declined by 64.4 percent to 96.8 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
But Chile's copper exports to China registered a 7.6 percent
rise, reaching 103.4 million dollars, according to the Central
Bank figures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
