<HEADLINE> Venezuela To Host Housing Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Housing
Conference will be held on July 19-22 in Margarita Island of
Venezuela, Miguel Rojas Naranjo, President of the Venezuelan
National Housing Council, said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
With some 300 delegates from 20 countries attending the
conference, Rojas said the main theme will be the possibilities of
housing financing in Latin America, and the long term outlook of
housing market development.
</P>
<P>
There will be 36 lectures during the four-day meeting, at which
participants will discuss themes related to different housing
policies being developed in the Latin American countries, and
changes in the financing organizations, such as banks and savings
and loans institutions.
</P>
<P>
Rojas said the conference will be an important event for the
national public sector, because the housing needs will be
discussed.
</P>
<P>
In Venezuela, most families in need of a house lack the
necessary resources, he noted. 
</P>
