<HEADLINE> Bonded Zone Attracts More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 11 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment in the
Zhangjiagang Bonded Zone in east China's Jiangsu Province has
continued to grow this year.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three overseas-funded enterprises were approved in the
zone in the first six months of the year, with overseas investment
totaling 105.6 million U.S dollars. These two figures were 10
percent and 40 percent higher than the same period of year.
</P>
<P>
To counter the effects of the Asian financial crisis, the zone
authorities of the city of Zhangjiagang on the lower reaches of
the Yangtze River, have turned to Europe and America for sources
of investment.
</P>
<P>
Efforts also have been made to improve the overall investment
environment in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are a total of 348 overseas-funded enterprises
in the zone, with contracted and already-paid overseas investment
totaling 1.47 billion U.S. dollars and 713 million U.S. dollars,
respectively. 
</P>
