<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Chilean Satellite Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The first Chilean satellite,
called Fasat-Bravo, was launched into space Friday at 02:32
Chilean time from the Baikonur cosmodrome in Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean Air Force said the satellite was launched by a
Ukrainian rocket Zenith II.
</P>
<P>
The Fasat-Bravo is expected to start emitting its signal within
the next 24 hours, marking the entrance of Chile into the space
race.
</P>
<P>
Attempts were made to put in orbit the Chilean satellite on
June 23 and 24 and on Thursday of this week, together with a
Russian satellite and other four microsatellites belonging to
Germany, Australia, Israel, and Thailand, but the launching was
delayed because of rocket failures.
</P>
<P>
Chile had tried to send a satellite into orbit on August 31,
1995 but failed because of a technical problem.
</P>
<P>
The Fasat-Bravo weighing 50 kilograms has the shape of a
60-centimeter cube with a 35-centimeter square base.
</P>
<P>
This miniprobe was built by Chilean and British technicians at
the Space Department of the University of Surrey in Great Britain.
</P>
<P>
The Fasat-Bravo will be used to monitor the ozone layer
permanently, remote-sense natural resources and provide education
and aeronautical communications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980711.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Warning Issued About Renewed Activity of Indonesia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 11 (Xinhua) -- A public warning about renewed
activity of Mount Merapi in Indonesia's central Java had been
issued by a local volcanological service, the local press reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The head of the Directorate of Volcanology's Yogyakarta office,
Mas Atje Purbawinata, told reporters that his office had raised
its state of alertness about the 2,968-meter volcano to the
highest level.
</P>
<P>
The volcano is about 20 kilometers from the ancient royal
capital of Yogyakarta, now a city of two million people.
</P>
<P>
Atje said several cracks created by internal pressure at the
top of the mountain had also been observed.
</P>
<P>
"Cracking is now taking place at the top, and we've been
monitoring the phenomenon closely," he said.
</P>
<P>
Since early Friday morning till noon, at least 10 tremors had
been recorded.
</P>
<P>
"This show that the magma activity is rising. We estimate that
the core of the activity is located about 300 meters below the tip
of the cone," Atje was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The office had also warned public authorities in areas around
the volcano to prepare for emergency action.
</P>
<P>
Measures already taken included warning residents in nearby
areas to get ready for evacuation and building dams to channel the
lava if it begins to flow, he said.
</P>
<P>
In various villages near Yogyakarta, emergency posts have been
set up to anticipate any possible situation which may arise.
</P>
<P>
The mountain, 400 kilometers east of Jakarta, is the most
active volcano in the country and one of the world's most active
volcanoes.
</P>
<P>
The last eruption was in January 1997, when more than 8,000
nearby villagers were evacuated after the volcano spewed hot gas,
ash and lava over its surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
Merapi's most destructive eruption this century was in 1930,
when 1,300 people were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
