<HEADLINE> Top Two Seeds Advance to Semi-finals at Czech Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Jana Novotna of Czech
Republic and second seed Sandrine Testud of France entered the
semi-finals after beating their respective rivals at the Czech
open women's tennis tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Novotna had a 6-3, 6-2 easy victory over Sarah Pitkowski of
France while Testud came fron behind to overpower sixth seed
Italian Silvia Farina 2-6, 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In other two quarter-finals, fourth-seeded Natasha Zvereva of
Belarus ousted eighth seed Amelie Mauresmo of France 6-3, 6-2 and
fifth seed Slovakian Henrietta Nagyova eliminted American Meghann
Shaughnessy 6-1, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
