were freed on Thursday by their captors in the southern Philippine
province of Lanao del Sur, the military said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard:
</P>
<P>
-- The military and Muslim rebels agreed to a temporary truce
Friday after a day-long battle in the southern Philippines that
left at least two farmers dead and a disputed number of combatants
killed or wounded. 
</P>
