<HEADLINE> U.S. Firm Buys Uruguayan Data Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. firm Exxel Group has
bought the Clearing de Informes, a commercial data bank of
Uruguay, to further expand its business in the South American
region, said the two companies Friday.
</P>
<P>
Although the amount of the deal was not disclosed, Clearing de
Informes director Jose luis Lorietto said that Exxel will become
the holder of most stock of the Uruguayan company.
</P>
<P>
The data bank provides services related to real estate, state
institutions, and any company that sells on credit and it has has
data of all the persons who request credit.
</P>
<P>
This is the second Exxel Group acquisition in Uruguay following
its recent purchase of the Devoto supermarkets chain at a cost of
100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
An Exxel spokesman said that the acquisition of the data bank
is part of its strategy to expand business in the South American
region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
