<HEADLINE> Guadeloupe May Stage 2000 Tour de France Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 Tour de France could start
on the Caribbean island of Guadeloupe, race organiser Jean Marie
Leblanc said in Dublin on Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Dublin, Leblanc said: "We are looking
at Guadeloupe. As with other promoters we are considering
something out of the ordinary for 2000. We are still studying the
prospects and the feasibility."
</P>
<P>
Transporting the Tour "caravan" of some 3,000 people and more
than 1,200 vehicles is a major consideration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
