<HEADLINE> Canadian Dollar Drops to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian dollar dropped 0.15
cents to 67.63 U.S. cents Friday, another record low for the
wobbly currency.
</P>
<P>
A weak unemployment report was all it took to once again drive
the Canadian loonie to a new low since it set an historic closing
low of 67.85 U.S. cents in mid-June, reports said.
</P>
<P>
On the North American markets, trades chose to interpret the
latest unemployment figures as evidence that the Canadian economy
is beginning to slow down, the reports noted.
</P>
<P>
Statistics Canada reported Friday that the country's
unemployment rate remained unchanged at 8.4 percent in June, but
there were about 36,000 fewer jobs across the country.
</P>
<P>
Only a decline in the number of people looking for work in June
kept the unemployment rate from climbing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
